definition.value: A hexynoic acid in which the triple bond is between the carbons at positions 5 and 6.
A dipeptide composed of L-glutamic acid and L-tryptophan joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-glutamic acid and L-tyrosine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of glycine and L-leucine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of glycine and L-histidine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of glycine and L-serine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of glycine and L-tyrosine joined by a peptide linkage.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-isoleucine, L-leucine and two L-tryptophan units joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-isoleucine, L-leucine, L-valine and L-tyrosine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide composed of L-isoleucine and L-histidine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-glutamic acid and L-lysine joined by a peptide linkage.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-leucine, two L-serine units and L-tyrosine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and L-serine residues.
A tripeptide composed of L-leucine L-alanine, and L-aspartic acid joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of L-leucine, L-alanine and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of L-leucine, L-alanine and glycine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide composed of L-leucine and L-alanine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-leucine and L-arginine joined by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide composed of L-leucine and L-asparagine joined by a peptide linkage.
A tripeptide composed of L-leucine, L-asparagine and L-histidine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide formed from two L-leucine residues.
A ribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the four triphosphate OH groups of N(6)-(dimethylallyl)adenosine 5'-triphosphate.
A ribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the three diphosphate OH groups of N(6)-(dimethylallyl)adenosine 5'-diphosphate.
A long chain fatty alcohol that is octadecanol containing two double bonds located at positions 9 and 12 (the 9Z,12Z-geoisomer).
A serine derivative that is L-serine in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a ureido group.
Any naphthyridine derivative that is a derivative of 1,8-naphthyridine.
Any naphthyridine derivative that is a derivative of 2,7-naphthyridine.
Any organonitrogen heterocyclic compound that is a derivative of a naphthyridine.
Any naphthyridine derivative that is a derivative of 1,5-naphthyridine.
A bicyclic organic group that contains both carbon and hetero atoms.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(1)-methylguanosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of 7-[(3S)-3-amino-3-carboxypropyl]wyosine residue.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of wybutosine 5'-monophosphate.
A quaternary ammonium salt that is the monoiodide salt of acetyl-beta-methylthiocholine.
A cysteine derivative that is the S-(2-amino-8-formyl-3-oxo-3H-phenoxazin-1-yl) derivative of N-acetyl-L-cysteine.
A nucleoside residue in which an adenosine residue has been modified by substitution at C-2 by a mercapto (sulfanyl) group and at the 6-amino nitrogen by a Delta(2)-isopentenyl group.
A cysteine derivative that is the S-(2-amino-8-carboxy-3-oxo-3H-phenoxazin-1-yl) derivative of N-acetyl-L-cysteine.
A 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propionic acid.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of 4-demethyl-7-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)wyosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A nucleoside analogue in which an adenosine residue has been modified by substitution at C-2 by a mercapto (sulfanyl) group and at the 6-amino nitrogen by a Delta(2)-isopentenyl group.
The nucleotide residue formed from 7-[(3S)-3-amino-3-carboxypropyl]wyosine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3' and 5' positions.
A ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is wyosine 5'-monophosphate substituted at position 7 by a 3-amino-3-carboxypropyl group.
A glycophytoceramide having a 6-deoxy-6-(N'-naphthoureido)-alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the O-1 position and a hexacosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 7-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)wyosine 5'-monophosphate.
The nucleotide residue formed from 4-demethyl-7-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)wyosine 5'-monophosphate with linkages at the 3' and 5' positions.
A ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having (2S)-2-amino-4-(6-methyl-9-oxo-4,9-dihydro-3H-imidazo[1,2-a]purin-7-yl)butanoic acid as the nucleobase.

A vitamin D that is calciol or its hydroxylated metabolites calcidiol and calcitriol. Calciol (also known as vitamin D3) acts as a hormone precursor, being hydroxylated in the liver to calcidiol (25-hydroxyvitamin D3), which is then further hydroxylated in the kidney to give calcitriol (1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3), the active hormone.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-demethyl-7-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)wyosine 5'-monophosphate.
A glycophytoceramide having a 6-deoxy-6-benzamido-alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the O-1 position and a hexacosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.
